From: pmOS Mi8Lite <macosmojave2@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] drm/msm/dpu: sdm660: disable idle_pc to keep panel on

With has_idle_pc=true the DPU collapses the INTF after the first frame when
there are no new commits, dropping the panel to black (backlight on). On
platina (Mi 8 Lite, video-mode TD4320) this leaves the screen black shortly
after boot. Disable idle power collapse so the INTF keeps scanning out.

Signed-off-by: pmOS Mi8Lite <macosmojave2@gmail.com>
---
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/disp/dpu1/catalog/dpu_3_2_sdm660.h	2026-06-18 09:10:09.528773239 -0500
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/disp/dpu1/catalog/dpu_3_2_sdm660.h	2026-06-18 09:10:09.538695329 -0500
@@ -11,7 +11,7 @@
 	.max_mixer_blendstages = 0x7,
 	.has_src_split = true,
 	.has_dim_layer = true,
-	.has_idle_pc = true,
+	.has_idle_pc = false,
 	.has_3d_merge = true,
 	.max_linewidth = DEFAULT_DPU_OUTPUT_LINE_WIDTH,
 	.pixel_ram_size = DEFAULT_PIXEL_RAM_SIZE,
